User Story 1: As a user, I want to add new tasks to my to-do list with a due date and priority. 

Acceptance criteria:  

The user should be able to enter a task description, due date, and priority level. 

The task should be added to the list and displayed in order of priority or due date. 

 

User Story 2: As a user, I want to edit existing tasks. 

Acceptance criteria:  

The user should be able to click or tap on a task to edit it. 

The user should be able to modify the task description, due date, and priority level. 

The edited task should be updated in the list and visually reflect the changes. 

 

User Story 3: As a user, I want to mark tasks as complete. 

Acceptance criteria:  

The user should be able to click or tap on a task to mark it as complete. 

The completed task should be visually indicated as completed and moved to a separate section. 

 

User Story 4: As a user, I want to delete tasks. 

Acceptance criteria:  

The user should be able to click or tap on a task to delete it. 

The deleted task should be removed from the list. 

 

User Story 5: As a user, I want to view my completed tasks. 

Acceptance criteria:  

The application should have a separate section to display completed tasks. 

The user should be able to navigate between the active and completed tasks easily. 